08/07/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Defence Minister Spilios Spiliotopoulos, accompanied by a high-level military delegation, left Thursday (8 July) for a two-day official visit to Tirana. 
He will meet with Albanian counterpart Pandeli Majko, President Alfred Moisiu and Prime Minister Fatos Nano. 
The focus will be on the possible expansion of bilateral defence co-operation, as well as regional security. 
(Kathimerini - 07/07/04)
